@@rThe Scorching Sands@@N

  A superheated dune-sea and ember-basin complex in the east-southeastern
desert, where failing institutions left behind route doctrine, ration
rites, and weaponized heat technology. Scorching Sands is not simply
hot desert. It is a @@ylegal and ecological pressure chamber@@N.

  Four micro-zones define the region. The @@rEmber Dunes@@N are tall red-gold
ridges whose leeward pockets trap lethal heat through the night. The
@@dKiln Basins@@N are blackened depressions where repeated firing events
left fractured ceramic debris and breath-burn wind. The @@eCinder
Channels@@N are dry distributary cuts used as convoy lanes -- sheltered
from wind but prone to ambush. The @@dAshglass Rims@@N are belts of
partially fused sand and brittle slag, foreshadowing the Saltglass
Reach's true Glasswind Belts to the east.

  In the Ledger Kingdom era, crown contractors built kiln houses here
to fire seal-ceramics and convoy fittings. Their innovation was
@@ysun-fired verification clay@@N -- shipment tags that changed color
irreversibly when exposed to tampering heat. This made Scorching Sands
a fraud-resistant certification district. The @@yBurn Ledger@@N -- a semi-
buried audit hall -- co-recorded kiln batches, water allocations, and
convoy fees in one archive.

  The @@yScorch Clause@@N is a contract rider still invoked by merchants:
cargo transiting the Sands claims supplemental water allocation, seal
materials must be heat-certified, and liability is allocated by route
segment rather than total journey. It is one of the earliest legal
mechanisms anticipating maritime-style risk segmentation.

  Three factions contest the region. @@eEmber Wardens@@N descend from route
inspectors and kiln officers, maintaining shade stations and enforcing
ration discipline. @@rAshbound Reavers@@N track convoy heat fatigue and
strike where water discipline breaks down. The @@dCauterist Synod@@N
interprets heat as purgative truth, branding false seals as heresy
and staging trial-by-sun rites at abandoned kiln mouths.

  Three daily heat phases govern survival. @@rHard Glare@@N brings surface
burns and strongest mirage shear. @@rBreathfire@@N traps basin heat in
lateral winds that sear lungs. @@dFalse Mercy@@N after dark masks residual
ground heat and delayed vent activity. Nights are safer from direct
sun but not always safer for contact or respiration.

  Heat here is @@radministrative pressure made physical@@N.
